        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 1:43PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 143 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Huntingdon, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntingdon, Bruceton, Vale, Hollow Rock, Henry, Clarksburg, Westport,
Hillard, Jumbo, Scott Hill, Leach, Mixie, Crews Store, Tate,
Garretsburg, Palmer Shelter, Ephesus, and Buena Vista.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for west
Tennessee.</instruction>
